    <fr:title text="Invertible maps are contractible › "><fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-002E.xml" title="Invertible maps are contractible" addr="//erct/erct-002E" type="local"><fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000W.xml" title="Inverse" addr="//erct/erct-000W" type="local">Invertible</fr:link> maps are <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="//erct/erct-001T" type="local">contractible</fr:link></fr:link> › </fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon  \colon  f\circ  f^{-1} = 1_{B}]]></fr:tex> be the counit of the <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000W.xml" title="Inverse" addr="//erct/erct-000W" type="local">inverse</fr:link> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex>. Given <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b:B]]></fr:tex>, we must show that the fiber of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001H.xml" title="Contractible type" addr="//erct/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link>; the centre of contraction is given by the pair 
 <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen f^{-1} x, \epsilon  x\right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
, and the required paths can be constructed via the <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001R.xml" title="Path object structure on fibers" addr="//erct/erct-001R" type="local">univalence principle for fibers</fr:link> using the unit <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta \colon  f^{-1}\circ  f = 1_{A}]]></fr:tex>, the coherence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi \colon  \mathsf {act}_{f}\circ \eta \sim \epsilon \circ  f]]></fr:tex>, and the <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001V.xml" title="Naturality of homotopies" addr="//erct/erct-001V" type="local">naturality of homotopies</fr:link>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter>
